    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>With Java 8:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String csv = String.join(\",\", ids);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>With Java 7-, there is a dirty way (<strong><em>note: it works only if you don't insert strings which contain <code>\", \"</code> in your list</em></strong>) - obviously, <code>List#toString</code> will perform a loop to create <code>idList</code> but it does not appear in your code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; ids = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\nids.add(\"1\");\nids.add(\"2\");\nids.add(\"3\");\nids.add(\"4\");\nString idList = ids.toString();\nString csv = idList.substring(1, idList.length() - 1).replace(\", \", \",\");\n</code></pre>\n"
