    "body" : "<p>If you're using <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/collections/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Eclipse Collections</a> (formerly GS Collections), you can use the <code>makeString()</code> method.</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; ids = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\nids.add(\"1\");\nids.add(\"2\");\nids.add(\"3\");\nids.add(\"4\");\n\nAssert.assertEquals(\"1,2,3,4\", ListAdapter.adapt(ids).makeString(\",\"));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you can convert your <code>ArrayList</code> to a <code>FastList</code>, you can get rid of the adapter.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Assert.assertEquals(\"1,2,3,4\", FastList.newListWith(1, 2, 3, 4).makeString(\",\"));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> I am a committer for Eclipse collections.</p>\n"
